# Disable SC2016: Expressions don't expand in single quotes.
# All single-quoted $var references in this repo are intentional jq variables,
# not missed shell expansions.
disable=SC2016

# Disable SC2034: Variable appears unused.
# Attack scripts set variables for use in sourced library scripts (_lib.sh,
# _crapi-lib.sh, etc.) and trap handlers. ShellCheck cannot follow sourced
# variable usage across files.
disable=SC2034

# Disable SC1091: Not following sourced file.
# Scripts source _lib.sh, _crapi-lib.sh, etc. via relative paths that
# ShellCheck cannot resolve in CI.
disable=SC1091

# Disable SC2064: Use single quotes for trap to prevent early expansion.
# Attack scripts intentionally expand variables at trap-set time to capture
# cleanup state.
disable=SC2064

# Disable SC2045: Iterating over ls output is fragile.
# Runner/orchestration scripts iterate over numbered test scripts; filenames
# are controlled and alphanumeric-only.
disable=SC2045

# Disable SC2002: Useless cat.
# Some pipelines use cat for readability in complex log-parsing chains.
disable=SC2002

# Disable SC2106: This only exits the subshell.
# Subshell-based parallelism in orchestration scripts is intentional.
disable=SC2106
